  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="9">CURATOR</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">The hypergeometric function 2F1(a,b;c;z) is characterized by the property 2F1(a,b;c;z) → 1 for a·b·z/c≪1 [30]. Taking cognizance of the characteristic resonance condition (21), one realizes that there are no confined stationary field configurations in the regime m2xm/τ≪1 [In this regime one finds 2F1≃1, whereas the resonance condition (21) for confined stationary states requires 2F1≃0]. In this section we would like to prove the (stronger) claim that there are no stationary confined field configurations for mirror radii in the regime xm/τ≪1</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">45</subfield>
  </datafield>
