    <subfield code="m">Note that the near-horizon region (35) corresponds to r - r+ ≪ r+ - r-, which implies ∆ ≃ (r - r+)(r+ - r-)</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">47</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">Note that y → -∞ (and thus eτy/M → 0) in the near-horizon region (35)</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">48</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">We recall that our analysis in this section is valid in the regime x/τ ≪ 1 [see Eq. (35)]. However, since λ = O(l2) [see Eq. (40)], the argument λ + τr+ 2M x τ of the Bessel function in (46) can be large in the asymptotic eikonal l ≫ 1 regime</subfield>
    <subfield code="o">49</subfield>
