  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">It is worth emphasizing again that this feature of the spinning black-hole-mirror-field bomb is a non-trivial one. In particular, it should be contrasted with the charged black-hole-mirrorfield bomb [6, 7]. It was previously shown [7] that, in the charged case, the stationary mirror radius, xstat m (qQ) [43], can be made arbitrarily small in the asymptotic qQ ≫ 1 regime (that is, in the charged case, the confining mirror can be placed arbitrarily close to the black-hole horizon [7])</subfield>
